Durable logs of Events
  - Append only
	- Can only seek by offset, not indexed 


KAFKA TOPIC - kind of data structure which main purpose is to store data(Messages/Events).

Data in topics can be of any format (Text(Json, xml), Binary(Avro, Protobuf))

Ways of accessing KAFKA TOPIC: CONSUMER and PRODUCER

Kafka topics are immutable

Kafka Topic and Partitions
--------------

Order is ensured within partition only

Messages added to partitions have an id and these id are called kafka OFFSETS

Note: Offsets are not being reused even if the the message was deleted from the topic

Note: Data is randomly assigned to a partition unless a key is provided


